  <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Process_Description">Process Description</span></h2>
  <p>ITIL presents Technical Management as a "function". It plays an important role in the management of the IT infrastructure. </p>
  <p>Many Technical Management activities are embedded in various other ITIL processes - but not all Technical Management activities. For this reason, at IT Process Maps we decided to introduce a Technical Management process as part of the ITIL Process Map which includes the Technical Management activities not covered in any other ITIL process. </p>
  <p>Technical Management activities embedded in other processes are shown there, with responsibility assigned to the Technical Analyst role. </p>
  <p>The process overview of <a href="/images/itilsonine.jpg" class="internal" title="Itil-technical-management.jpg">ITIL Technical Management</a> shows the key information flows. </p>
  <p>&#160;</p>
  <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Sub-Processes">Sub-Processes</span></h2>
  <p>No sub-processes are specified for <a class="mw-selflink selflink">ITIL Technical Management</a>. </p>
  <p>&#160;</p>
  <h2><span id="Roles_|_Responsibilities"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Roles_.7C_Responsibilities">Roles | Responsibilities</span></h2>
  <p><b><span id="Technical_Analyst">Technical Analyst - Process Owner</span></b> </p>
  <ul>
    <li>The Technical Analyst is a Technical Management role which provides technical expertise and support for the management of the IT infrastructure. There is typically one Technical Analyst or team of analysts for every key technology area. This role plays an important part in the technical aspects of designing, testing, operating and improving IT services. It is also responsible for developing the skills required to operate the IT infrastructure.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>&#160;</p>
